'''Cloud Cuckoo Land''' refers to an idealistic state where everything is perfect - "You're living in Cloud-cuckoo-land".  The reference is to the play by the [[Athenian]] playwright [[Aristophanes]], ''[[The Birds (play)|The Birds]]'', in which the birds of the title, tired of the Earth and [[Olympus]], decide to erect a perfect city between the clouds, to be named Cloud-Cuckoo-Land (''Nephelokykkygia'').
